description:
Optimize KanbanBoard layout for mobile devices.

## Problem
6 columns side-by-side don't fit on mobile. Horizontal scrolling is poor UX.

## Solution
Vertical column stack on mobile, horizontal on desktop.

## Implementation

### Desktop (≥768px)
```css
.kanban-board {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
```

### Mobile (<768px)
```css
.kanban-board {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}
.kanban-column {
  width: 100%;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
```

### Collapsible Columns
- Each column is collapsible on mobile
- Tap column header to expand/collapse
- Remember expanded state in localStorage

### Column Navigation
- Sticky column navigation bar at top
- Quick jump to specific column
- Show task counts per column

## Success Criteria
- Kanban usable on phone screens
- No horizontal scrolling on mobile
- Quick access to all columns
- Column state persists

Replace 5s polling with Server-Sent Events for real-time updates.

## Why SSE?
- Lower latency (push vs poll)
- Less bandwidth (only send changes)
- Better UX (instant updates)
- Better mobile (fewer network requests)

## Architecture

### Server (app/api/events/stream/route.ts)
```typescript
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const stream = new ReadableStream({
    start(controller) {
      // Store connection
      connections.add(controller);

      // Send connected event
      controller.enqueue('event: connected\ndata: {}\n\n');

      // Cleanup on disconnect
      request.signal.addEventListener('abort', () => {
        connections.delete(controller);
      });
    }
  });

  return new Response(stream, {
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'text/event-stream',
      'Cache-Control': 'no-cache',
      'Connection': 'keep-alive',
    }
  });
}
```

### Broadcast Helper
```typescript
export function broadcastEvent(type: string, data: any) {
  const event = `event: ${type}\ndata: ${JSON.stringify(data)}\n\n`;
  for (const controller of connections) {
    try {
      controller.enqueue(new TextEncoder().encode(event));
    } catch {
      connections.delete(controller);
    }
  }
}
```

### Client (ObjectivesView)
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const eventSource = new EventSource('/api/events/stream');

  eventSource.addEventListener('task.updated', (e) => {
    const task = JSON.parse(e.data);
    updateTask(task);
  });

  eventSource.addEventListener('task.created', (e) => {
    const task = JSON.parse(e.data);
    addTask(task);
  });

  return () => eventSource.close();
}, []);
```

## Event Types
- task.updated - Task fields changed
- task.created - New task created
- task.deleted - Task deleted
- activity.logged - New activity entry

## Reconnection Logic
- Auto-reconnect on disconnect
- Exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s, max 30s)
- Show 'Reconnecting...' indicator

## Success Criteria
- SSE connection established on page load
- Task updates appear instantly (<100ms)
- Auto-reconnects on network failure
- Works across tab syncs
